DataElement.preferredName: Bone Marrow Biopsy Dry Tap Procedure Indicator
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Indicator of whether or not the bone marrow biopsy procedure resulted in a dry tap.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Bone Marrow Biopsy Dry Tap Procedure
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A biopsy involving the removal of a core tissue containing bone spicules and hematopoietic elements embedded in the marrow stroma.  This procedure is done in the hip area mainly for the diagnosis and evaluation of neoplastic and non-neoplastic hematopoietic disorders (e.g. anemias, leukemias, lymphomas) and the evaluation of the spread of solid tumors (e.g. carcinomas, sarcomas) and lymphomas for therapeutic purposes.:A bone marrow aspiration that does not yield any bone marrow material._Any stepwise set of actions.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: The removal of a small sample of bone marrow (usually from the hip) through a needle for examination under a microscope to see whether cancer cells are present.

Concepts.definition: A biopsy involving the removal of a core tissue containing bone spicules and hematopoietic elements embedded in the marrow stroma.  This procedure is done in the hip area mainly for the diagnosis and evaluation of neoplastic and non-neoplastic hematopoietic disorders (e.g. anemias, leukemias, lymphomas) and the evaluation of the spread of solid tumors (e.g. carcinomas, sarcomas) and lymphomas for therapeutic purposes.

Property.preferredName: Dry Tap Bone Marrow Aspiration Procedure
Property.preferredDefinition: A bone marrow aspiration that does not yield any bone marrow material._Any stepwise set of actions.

Concepts.definition: A bone marrow aspiration that does not yield any bone marrow material.
